{"title_page": "Mike Perry (fighter)", "text_new": "{{short description|American mixed martial arts fighter}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Mike Perry\n| other_names     = [[Florida Man]]<br>Platinum<ref name=\"TapologyProfile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/fighters/78335-mike-perry|title=Mike Perry, Tapology fighter page|publisher=tapology.com. Retrieved April 9, 2020}}</ref><br>Platinum Dioxide\n| caption         = Mike Perry in his boxing debut against Kenneth McNeil at \"Island Fights 33\"\n| birth_name      = \n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1991|09|15}}\n| birth_place     = [[Flint, Michigan]], United States\n| partner         = \n| residence       = [[Orlando, Florida]], United States\n| nationality     = African-American\n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=10}}<ref name=\"TapologyProfile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tapology.com/fightcenter/fighters/78335-mike-perry|title=Mike Perry, Tapology fighter page|publisher=tapology.com}}</ref>\n| weight          = {{convert|169|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Welterweight (MMA)|Welterweight]] (2015\u2013present)<br>[[Lightweight (MMA)|Lightweight]] (2014\u20132015)\n| reach           = 71 in<ref name=\"TapologyProfile\"/><ref name=UFCprofile>{{cite web|url=http://www.ufc.com/fighter/mike-perry|title=Mike Perry - Official UFC Profile|publisher=UFC.com|accessdate=December 23, 2016}}</ref>\n| style           =\n| rank            = Purple belt in [[Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BXxTLbUg9ST|title=\"Coaches #JulienWilliams and #PaulRodriguez both very experienced black belts and the best grapplers I know gave me my purple belt...\"|publisher=Instagram|author=platinummikeperry|date=August 14, 2017|accessdate=December 16, 2017}}</ref>\n| stance          = \n| team            = Fusion XL Academy<ref>https://mmajunkie.com/2018/05/mike-perry-moves-to-jackson-wink-mma-for-portion-of-ufc-226-training-camp</ref>\n| trainer         = \n| years_active    = 2014\u2013present\n| box_win         = 0\n| box_kowin       = 0\n| box_loss        = 1\n| box_koloss      = 1\n| box_draw        = \n| box_nc          = \n| mma_kowin       = 11\n| mma_subwin      = \n| mma_decwin      = 2\n| mma_koloss      = 1\n| mma_subloss     = 1\n| mma_decloss     = 4\n| mma_draw        = \n| mma_nc          = \n| am_win          = 8\n| am_kowin        = \n| am_loss         = 3\n| url             = \n| boxrec          = 716301\n| sherdog         = 176179\n}}\n\n'''Michael Joseph Perry''' (born September 15, 1991) is an American professional mixed martial artist and former professional boxer currently competing in the [[Welterweight (MMA)|welterweight]] division of the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]].\n\n==Background==\nPerry was born in [[Flint, Michigan]] on September 15, 1991. For much of his life, he moved around to different schools between Michigan and Florida. This instability led him to a path of drugs, house arrest, probation violation, and jail.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nagal|first1=Kyle|title=Fight Path: Mike Perry pushed through rocky patch to get to a life of MMA|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2015/07/fight-path-mike-perry-pushed-through-rocky-patch-to-get-to-a-life-of-mma|website=MMAjunkie|accessdate=14 October 2016}}</ref> Perry started training boxing at age 11, which led to his career in MMA.<ref name=UFCprofile />\n\n==Mixed martial arts career==\n===Early career===\nPerry made his professional debut in September 2014, after completing 11 amateur fights with a record of 8-3.<ref name=UFCprofile /> He competed for several regional promotions across the United States.  In just under two years, he fought nine times while finishing all of his opponents via KO/TKO.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mixedmartialarts.com/fighter/Mike-Perry:D6B91A26218099B7|title=The underground profile|work=mixedmartialarts.com |date=2016-10-08 |accessdate=2016-10-15}}</ref>\n\n===Ultimate Fighting Championship===\nPerry made his UFC debut on short notice against [[Lim Hyun-gyu]] on August 20, 2016, at [[UFC 202]], after [[Sultan Aliev]] pulled out due to injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fightsports.tv/story/32686695/mike-perry-replaces-aliev-at-ufc-202|title=Mike Perry replaces Aliev at UFC 202|publisher=fightsports.tv|author=Staff|date=2016-08-04|accessdate=2016-08-04|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822170653/http://www.fightsports.tv/story/32686695/mike-perry-replaces-aliev-at-ufc-202|archivedate=2016-08-22}}</ref> At the official weigh-ins, Perry faked a handshake with Lim then put his hands up like an old school boxer yelling to Lim, \"You thought you had a friend, boy!\" before screaming passionately at his opponent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbssports.com/mma/news/ufc-202-mike-perry-makes-impressive-debut-with-brutal-first-round-knockout/|title=UFC 202: Mike Perry makes impressive debut with brutal first round knockout|work=CBSSports.com|access-date=2017-06-09|language=en}}</ref> He defeated Lim via TKO in the first round after Perry dropped him twice with right hands, dropped him again with a left hook and then followed up with ground and pound before the referee jumped in to stop the fight.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2016/8/20/12571932/ufc-202-results-mike-perry-power-punches-his-way-to-tko-win-over-hyun|title=UFC 202 results: Mike Perry power punches his way to TKO win over Hyun Gyu Lim|publisher=mmafighting.com |author=Dave Doyle|date=2016-08-20|accessdate=2016-10-15}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Danny Roberts (fighter)|Danny Roberts]] on October 8, 2016, at [[UFC 204]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/danny-roberts-fight-ufc-204-11802884|title=Danny Roberts to fight at UFC 204 in Manchester against unbeaten Mike Perry |author=Joe Rimmer|publisher=liverpoolecho.co.uk|date=2016-08-26|accessdate=2016-08-26}}</ref> At the official weigh-ins Perry took a bite from a bar of chocolate and then told Roberts he was going to eat him alive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://craziestsportsfights.com/moment-missed-mike-perrys-ufc-204-weigh/|title=The Moment You Probably Missed During Mike Perry\u2019s UFC 204 Weigh-in|author=Sami Chamoun|publisher=craziestsportsfights.com|date=2016-10-12|accessdate=2017-05-15}}{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He defeated Roberts via KO late in the third round after Perry hurt him with a knee from the clinch, dropped him with a right hand and then followed up with ground and pound before the referee jumped in to stop the fight.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mmajunkie.com/2016/10/ufc-204-results-mike-perry-finishes-danny-roberts-with-20-seconds-left-in-fight-courtesy-of-knee|title=UFC 204 results: Mike Perry finishes Danny Roberts with 20 seconds left in fight courtesy of knee|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Ben Fowlkes|date=2016-10-08|accessdate=2016-10-15}}</ref> The referee Marc Goddard appeared to stop the fight late, issuing an apology after the event via Twitter.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mmajunkie.com/2016/10/ref-marc-goddard-weighs-on-his-late-stoppage-in-ufc-204s-perry-roberts-bout|title=Ref Marc Goddard weighs in on his late stoppage in UFC 204's Perry-Roberts bout|publisher=mmajunkie.com |author=MMAjunkie Staff|date=2016-10-10|accessdate=2017-05-15}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Alan Jouban]], on December 17, 2016, at [[UFC on Fox 22]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2016/12/ufc-on-fox-22-results-disciplined-alan-jouban-tops-mike-perry-in-main-card-opener|title=Alan Jouban vs. Mike Perry added to UFC Sacramento card|publisher=dailynews.com|author=Brian Martin|date=2016-10-17|accessdate=2016-10-17}}</ref> At the official weigh-ins Perry took a polaroid photo of Jouban and then tried to hand the photo to him as they traded words, but Jouban slapped it away with his hand and Perry aggressively feigned movement towards him while sticking his tongue out.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thescore.com/mma/news/1185473-ufc-sacramento-weigh-ins-feature-photoshoot-dance-off|title=UFC Sacramento weigh-ins feature photoshoot, dance-off|publisher=thescore.com|author=Themistoklis Alexis|date=2016-12-17|accessdate=2017-05-15}}</ref> He lost the fight by unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mmajunkie.com/2016/12/ufc-on-fox-22-results-disciplined-alan-jouban-tops-mike-perry-in-main-card-opener|title=UFC on FOX 22 results: Disciplined Alan Jouban tops Mike Perry in main-card opener|publisher=mmajunkie.com |author=Ben Fowlkes|date=2016-12-17|accessdate=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Jake Ellenberger]] on April 22, 2017, at [[UFC Fight Night 108]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2017/3/3/14799160/jake-ellenberger-vs-mike-perry-set-for-ufc-nashville|title=Jake Ellenberger vs. Mike Perry set for UFC Nashville|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Dave Doyle|date=2017-03-03|accessdate=2017-03-03}}</ref> He defeated Ellenberger via KO in the second round after Perry dropped him with a left hook early in round two then finished with a standing elbow from the clinch 30 seconds later.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2017/04/ufc-fight-night-108-results-mike-perry-ko-elbow-jake-ellenberger|title=UFC Fight Night 108 results: Mike Perry knocks out Jake Ellenberger with devastating elbow|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Ben Fowlkes|date=2017-04-23|accessdate=2017-04-23}}</ref> Perry was awarded a $50,000 ''Performance of the Night'' bonus.<ref name=\"Tristen Critchfield\">{{cite news|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/news/UFC-Fight-Night-108-Bonuses-Swanson-Lobov-Perry-Moreno-Garner-3650K-Checks-120567|title=UFC Fight Night 108 bonuses: Swanson, Lobov, Perry, Moreno garner $50K checks|publisher=sherdog.com|author=Tristen Critchfield|date=2017-04-23|accessdate=2017-04-23}}</ref>\n\nPerry was expected to face [[Thiago Alves (fighter)|Thiago Alves]] on September 16, 2017, at [[UFC Fight Night 116]]. Alves was pulled from the event and was replaced by newcomer Alex Reyes.<ref name=\"twobouts\">{{cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2017/7/19/15998858/alves-vs-perry-lombard-vs-smith-slated-for-ufn-pittsburgh|title=Alves vs. Perry, Lombard vs. Smith slated for UFN: Pittsburgh|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Ariel Helwani|date=2017-07-19|accessdate=2017-07-19}}</ref> He won the fight via knockout.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bjpenn.com/mma-news/ufc-pittsburgh/ufc-fight-night-116-results-mike-perry-kos-alex-reyes-video/|title=UFC Fight Night 116 Results: Mike Perry KO's Alex Reyes (VIDEO) {{!}} BJPenn.com|date=2017-09-16|work={{!}} BJPenn.com|access-date=2017-09-17|language=en-US}}</ref> The win also earned Perry his second ''Performance of the Night'' bonus award.<ref name=\"Mazique\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/brianmazique/2017/09/17/ufc-fight-night-116-results-bonus-winners-fight-scores-highlights-attendance-gate-info/#15c522042f1d|title=UFC Fight Night 116 Results, Bonus Winners, Fight Scores, Highlights, Attendance & Gate Info|last=Mazique|first=Brian|work=Forbes|access-date=2017-09-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Santiago Ponzinibbio]] on December 16, 2017, at [[UFC on Fox: Lawler vs. dos Anjos]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmabrasil.com.br/santiago-ponzinibbio-enfrenta-mike-perry-no-ufc-on-fox-26|title=Santiago Ponzinibbio enfrenta Mike Perry no UFC On Fox 26|date=2017-10-13|work=MMA Brasil|access-date=2017-10-13|language=pt-BR}}</ref> He lost the fight by unanimous decision.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2017/12/ufc-on-fox-26-results-santiago-ponzinibbio-edges-mike-perry-in-3-round-thriller|title=UFC on FOX 26 results: Santiago Ponzinibbio edges Mike Perry in 3-round thriller|date=2017-12-17|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2017-12-17|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Max Griffin (fighter)|Max Griffin]] on February 24, 2018 at [[UFC on Fox: Emmett vs. Stephens]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Mike-Perry-Gets-Hometown-Duty-Versus-Max-Griffin-at-UFC-on-Fox-28-in-Orlando-130947|title=Mike Perry gets hometown duty versus Max Griffin at UFC on Fox 28 in Orlando|publisher=sherdog.com|author=Jordan Breen|date=2018-01-08|accessdate=2018-01-08}}</ref> He lost the fight via unanimous decision.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/02/ufc-on-fox-28-results-heavy-underdog-max-griffin-works-over-mike-perry-upset-orlando-mma|title=UFC on FOX 28 results: Heavy underdog Max Griffin works over Mike Perry for upset|date=2018-02-25|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2018-02-25|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nPerry was expected to face [[Yancy Medeiros]] on July 7, 2018 at [[UFC 226]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2018/4/17/17249316/mike-perry-vs-yancy-medeiros-slated-for-ufc-226|title=Mike Perry vs. Yancy Medeiros slated for UFC 226|work=MMA Fighting|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> However, Medeiros pulled out of the fight on June 27 citing a rib injury. The following day, it was announced that [[Paul Felder]] would step in to face Perry in a Welterweight bout at the same event.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/06/yancy-medeiros-injured-out-ufc-226-mike-perry-replacement-needed|title=Yancy Medeiros out of UFC 226; replacement needed for Mike Perry|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Mike Bohn and John Morgan|date=2018-06-28|access-date=2018-06-28}}</ref> Perry won the fight via split decision.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloodyelbow.com/2018/7/7/17544640/ufc-226-results-mike-perry-vs-paul-felder-mma-news|title=UFC 226 results: Mike Perry gets past Paul Felder in grueling, bloody battle|work=Bloody Elbow|access-date=2018-07-08}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Donald Cerrone]] on November 10, 2018 at [[UFC Fight Night 139]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/07/donald-cerrone-vs-mike-perry-booked-ufc-denver|title=Donald Cerrone, Mike Perry to throw down at UFC Denver|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=John Morgan|date= 2018-07-20|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref> Perry lost the fight via submission due to an armbar in round one, marking the first time he's been finished in a professional mixed martial arts fight.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lowkickmma.com/highlights-donald-cerrone-taps-mike-perry/|title=Highlights: Donald Cerrone Taps Mike Perry|last=Ravens|first=Andrew|date=2018-11-11|work=LowKickMMA.com|access-date=2018-11-11|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAfter the fight with Cerrone, Perry signed a new contract with the UFC and faced [[Alex Oliveira (fighter)|Alex Oliveira]] on April 27, 2019 at [[UFC Fight Night: Jacar\u00e9 vs. Hermansson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2019/04/mike-perry-plans-controversy-weight-cut-ufc-on-espn-plus-8|title=Mike Perry plans to 'spark some controversy' after tough weight cut for UFC on ESPN+ 8|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Mike Bohn|date=April 25, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"perry\">>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Mike-Perry-Replaces-Jingliang-Li-Meets-Alex-Oliveira-at-UFC-on-ESPN-3-in-Fort-Lauderdale-151899|title=Mike Perry Replaces Jingliang Li, Meets Alex Oliveira at UFC on ESPN 3 in Fort Lauderdale|author=Tristen Critchfield|publisher=sherdog|access-date=2019-03-27}}</ref> He won the back-and-forth fight by unanimous decision. The win also earned Perry his first ''Fight of the Night'' bonus award.<ref name=\"MMA Junkie Staff\">{{Cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2019/04/ufc-on-espn-8-bonus-of-course-mike-perry-and-alex-oliveira-were-fight-of-the-night|title=UFC on ESPN+ 8 bonuses: Of course Mike Perry and Alex Oliveira were 'Fight of the Night'|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=MMA Junkie Staff|date=2019-04-27|access-date=2019-04-28}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Vicente Luque]] on August 10, 2019 at [[UFC on ESPN+ 14]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Vicente-Luque-to-Meet-Mike-Perry-in-UFC-Uruguay-CoHeadliner-on-Aug-10-157699|title=Vicente Luque to meet Mike Perry in UFC Uruguay co-headliner on Aug. 10|publisher=sherdog.com|author=Tristen Critchfield|date=2019-07-03|accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref> He lost the fight via split decision.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cagesidepress.com/2019/08/10/ufc-uruguay-results-vicente-luque-mike-perry-split-decision/|title=UFC Uruguay Results: Vicente Luque Battles Mike Perry to Bloody Split-Decision Win|last=Harshman|first=Heath|date=2019-08-10|website=Cageside Press|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-11}}</ref>  This fight earned him the ''[[List of UFC bonus award recipients|Fight of the Night]]'' award.<ref name=\"ESPN+ 14\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmanews.com/ufc-uruguay-bonuses-attendance-revealed/|title=UFC Uruguay Bonuses & Attendance Revealed \u2022 MMA News|author=Fernando Quiles Jr.|date=2019-08-11|publisher=mmanews.com|access-date=2019-08-11}}</ref> As a result, Perry was expected to be sidelined for the remainder of 2019 after undergoing surgery to correct facial injuries sustained during the Luque fight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.usatoday.com/2019/08/mike-perry-nose-surgery-vicente-luque-ufc-on-espn-plus-14-uruguay|title=Mike Perry facing lengthy recovery timeline after surgery for broken nose|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Mike Bohn|date=2018-08-11|accessdate=2019-08-11}}</ref>\n\nPerry faced [[Geoff Neal]] on December 14, 2019 at [[UFC 245]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mmafighting.com/2019/10/31/20942072/mike-perry-geoff-neal-ufc-245-december-las-vegas|title=Mike Perry vs. Geoff Neal booked for UFC 245 in December|last=Cruz|first=Guilherme|date=2019-10-31|website=MMA Fighting|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> He lost the bout via first round technical knockout.\n\n==Controversy==\nDuring his UFC debut at [[UFC 202]] Perry and his cornerman, former UFC middleweight Alex Nicholson, were accused of racism after Nicholson shouted during the pre-fight introductions, saying, \"He can't even open his motherf--king eyes.\" referring to his Korean opponent [[Hyun Gyu Lim]]. Nicholson later addressed the comment on Twitter, saying, \"I respect every man who steps in the cage and my comments were insensitive towards Lim (sic) I was hype for my brother but It's all love no hate.\" Nicholson also referred to Lim as \"Dung Him Kong Jung Foo,\" in a Facebook post. On the Monday following the fight Perry offered an explanation while on ''The MMA Hour'' stating \"I don't think any of my competition can see me, and when I hit Lim, I opened a lot of people's eyes,\" Perry told [[Ariel Helwani]]. Helwani then clarified that the comment was made prior to the fight to which Perry responded \"Well, we can see the future.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloodyelbow.com/2016/8/24/12628576/mike-perry-defends-racist-taunts-i-dont-believe-there-was-harm-intended-ufc-news|title=Mike Perry defends corner's racist taunts: 'I don\u2019t believe there was any harm intended'|work=Bloody Elbow|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloodyelbow.com/2016/9/1/12757580/ufc-202-mma-news-alex-nicholson-fighter-hyun-gyu-lim-racist-remarks|title=UFC issue statement on Nicholson\u2019s racial remarks|work=Bloody Elbow|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mmamania.com/2016/8/22/12585404/audio-heres-the-racist-remark-that-has-one-ufc-fighter-in-hot-water-mma|title=Cries Of Racism Overshadow UFC Win|work=MMAmania.com|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2660309-ufc-remains-blissfully-indifferent-to-bigotry-after-mike-perrys-corner-fiasco|title=UFC Remains Blissfully Indifferent to Bigotry After Mike Perry's Corner Fiasco|publisher=[[Bleacher Report]]|author=Sydnie Jones|date=2016-08-30|accessdate=2017-04-24}}</ref> Perry has also been criticized for making [[homophobic]] and racist comments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2705213-ufc-fight-night-108-results-the-real-winners-and-losers-from-nashville|title=UFC Fight Night 108 Results: The Real Winners and Losers from Nashville|publisher=[[Bleacher Report]]|author=Nathan McCarter|date=2017-04-23|accessdate=2017-04-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloodyelbow.com/2018/5/25/17396200/ufc-mike-perry-once-again-uses-n-word-tyron-woodley-gives-him-pass-race-mma-news|title=Mike Perry once again uses \u2018n-word,\u2019 Tyron Woodley gives him a pass on it|work=Bloody Elbow|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/10/ufc-fight-night-139-mike-perry-native-american-promo-video|title=Oh no, Mike Perry, what are you even doing with this promo, man?|publisher=[[MMAjunkie.com]]|author=Ben Fowlkes|date=2018-10-30|accessdate=2018-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadspin.com/dumbest-man-in-mma-cuts-extremely-racist-promo-video-1830105459|title=Dumbest Man In MMA Cuts Extremely Racist Promo Video|publisher=[[Deadspin]]|author=Patrick Redford|date=2018-10-30|accessdate=2018-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2018/10/30/ufc-fighter-under-fire-for-racist-native-american-promo-video/|title=UFC fighter under fire for \u2018racist\u2019 Native American promo video|publisher=[[New York Post]]|author=Chris Perez|date=2018-10-30|accessdate=2018-11-16}}</ref>\n\n==Championships and accomplishments==\n*'''[[Ultimate Fighting Championship]]'''\n**[[List of UFC bonus award recipients|Performance of the Night]] (Two times) <small>vs. [[Jake Ellenberger]], Alex Reyes</small><ref name=\"Tristen Critchfield\"/><ref name=\"Mazique\"/>\n**[[List of UFC bonus award recipients|Fight of the Night]] (Two times) {{small|vs. [[Alex Oliveira (fighter)|Alex Oliveira]] and [[Vicente Luque]]}}<ref name=\"MMA Junkie Staff\"/><ref name=\"ESPN+ 14\" />\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n{{MMArecordbox\n| draws= \n| nc= \n| ko-wins= 11\n| sub-wins= 0\n| dec-wins= 2\n| ko-losses= 1\n| sub-losses= 1\n| dec-losses= 4\n| dq-wins= \n| dq-losses= \n| other-wins= \n| other-losses= \n}}\n{{MMA record start}}\n|-\n|{{no2}}Loss\n|align=center|13\u20136\n|[[Geoff Neal]]\n|TKO (head kick and punches)\n|[[UFC 245]] \n|{{dts|2019|December|14}}\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|1: